0
00:01:42,549 --> 00:01:45,085
Hi, everybody. This is your cousin Brucie. Whoa!

1
00:01:45,151 --> 00:01:49,189
Our summer romances are in full bloom, and everybody's in love!

2
00:01:49,289 --> 00:01:52,358
So cousins, here's a great song from the Four Seasons.

3
00:01:59,666 --> 00:02:02,469
That was the summer of 1963...

4
00:02:02,502 --> 00:02:06,106
when everybody called me ""Baby"" and it didn't occur to me to mind.

5
00:02:15,014 --> 00:02:17,150
That was before President Kennedy was shot...

6
00:02:17,217 --> 00:02:19,185
before the Beatles came...

7
00:02:19,285 --> 00:02:21,354
when I couldn't wait to join the Peace Corps...

8
00:02:21,421 --> 00:02:25,325
and I thought I'd never find a guy as great as my dad.

9
00:02:34,834 --> 00:02:37,370
That was the summer we went to Kellerman's.

10
00:02:56,589 --> 00:02:59,592
Ping-Pong in the west arcade, softball in the east diamond.

11
00:02:59,692 --> 00:03:01,928
All you Sandy Koufaxes, get out there!

12
00:03:02,028 --> 00:03:04,464
Complimentary dance lessons in the gazebo.

13
00:03:04,531 --> 00:03:07,167
Oh, my God. Look at that!

14
00:03:07,233 --> 00:03:11,371
Mom, I should've brought the coral shoes. You said I was taking too much.

15
00:03:11,438 --> 00:03:14,074
Well, sweetheart, you brought ten pairs.

16
00:03:14,174 --> 00:03:16,643
But the coral shoes matched that dress.

17
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:18,378
This is not a tragedy.

18
00:03:18,445 --> 00:03:22,916
A tragedy is three men trapped in a mine or police dogs used in Birmingham.

19
00:03:22,982 --> 00:03:25,185
Monks burning themselves in protest.

20
00:03:25,251 --> 00:03:26,653
Butt out, Baby.

21
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:30,457
Okay, we got horseshoes on the south lawn in 15 minutes!

22
00:03:30,557 --> 00:03:33,493
We've got splish-splash the water class down by the lake.

23
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:37,197
We have the still life art class. We got volleyball and croquet.

24
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:39,799
And for you older folks, we got sacks!

25
00:03:42,569 --> 00:03:42,569
Doc!

26
00:03:42,569 --> 00:03:43,903
Doc!

27
00:03:44,637 --> 00:03:45,839
Max!

28
00:03:45,939 --> 00:03:50,677
Doc, after all these years I finally got you up on my mountain.

29
00:03:51,578 --> 00:03:53,012
How's the blood pressure?

30
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:55,014
I want you girls to know...

31
00:03:55,081 --> 00:03:58,485
if it were not for this man, I'd be standing here dead.

32
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:01,755
- Billy, get the bags. - Right away, Doc.

33
00:04:01,821 --> 00:04:05,024
I kept the best cabin for you and your beautiful girls.

34
00:04:08,795 --> 00:04:10,930
Hey, thanks a lot.

35
00:04:10,997 --> 00:04:12,699
You want a job here?

36
00:04:12,799 --> 00:04:15,935
There's a merengue class in the gazebo in the next few minutes.

37
00:04:16,002 --> 00:04:18,705
The greatest teacher. Used to be a Rockette.

38
00:04:18,805 --> 00:04:22,776
It's his first real vacation in six years, Max. Take it easy.

39
00:04:22,842 --> 00:04:25,712
Three weeks here, it'll feel like a year.

40
00:04:25,812 --> 00:04:29,349
One, two, three, four! Stomp those grapes and stomp some more!

41
00:04:29,449 --> 00:04:33,586
One, two, three, four! Listen to the music!

42
00:04:33,653 --> 00:04:35,055
Sorry.

43
00:04:35,155 --> 00:04:36,890
Move your caboose and shake it loose!

44
00:04:36,990 --> 00:04:40,794
One, two, three, four! Start the train!

45
00:04:45,298 --> 00:04:48,068
Come on, men! Follow me into a round robin!

46
00:04:49,135 --> 00:04:51,371
Ladies, the inner circle!

47
00:05:01,448 --> 00:05:03,016
Come on, ladies!

48
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:07,520
God wouldn't have given you maracas if he didn't want you to shake them!

49
00:05:11,858 --> 00:05:14,627
Okay now, ladies, when I say ""stop""...

50
00:05:14,694 --> 00:05:17,697
you're gonna find the man of your dreams.

51
00:05:18,765 --> 00:05:20,033
Stop!

52
00:05:21,735 --> 00:05:25,839
Remember, he's the boss on the dance floor, if nowhere else.

53
00:05:34,714 --> 00:05:37,951
Mom, Dad, I'm going up to the main house to look around.

54
00:06:15,588 --> 00:06:18,291
There are two kinds of help here.

55
00:06:18,391 --> 00:06:20,560
You waiters are all college guys...

56
00:06:20,627 --> 00:06:24,531
and I went to Harvard and Yale to hire you.

57
00:06:24,597 --> 00:06:27,567
And why did I do that? Why?

58
00:06:28,968 --> 00:06:31,771
I shouldn't have to remind you. This is a family place.

59
00:06:31,838 --> 00:06:35,642
That means you keep your fingers out of the water, hair out of the soup...

60
00:06:35,742 --> 00:06:37,911
and show the goddamn daughters a good time.

61
00:06:38,745 --> 00:06:40,146
All the daughters.

62
00:06:41,648 --> 00:06:43,817
Even the dogs.

63
00:06:43,917 --> 00:06:46,653
Schlepp 'em out to the terrace, show 'em the stars.

64
00:06:46,753 --> 00:06:49,022
- Romance 'em any way you want. - Got that, guys?

65
00:06:49,122 --> 00:06:51,091
Hey, hold it! Hold it.

66
00:06:52,992 --> 00:06:56,629
Well, if it isn't the entertainment staff.

67
00:06:56,663 --> 00:06:58,998
Listen, wise ass, you got your own rules.

68
00:06:59,099 --> 00:07:01,267
Dance with the daughters. Teach 'em the mambo...

69
00:07:01,334 --> 00:07:03,970
the cha-cha, anything they pay for.

70
00:07:04,037 --> 00:07:05,638
That's it.

71
00:07:05,739 --> 00:07:07,907
That's where it ends.

72
00:07:07,974 --> 00:07:11,644
No funny business, no conversations, and keep you hands off!

73
00:07:14,547 --> 00:07:18,218
It's the same at all these places. Some ass in the woods, but no conversation.

74
00:07:18,318 --> 00:07:20,220
Watch it, Rodriguez.

75
00:07:22,455 --> 00:07:26,359
Can you keep that straight, Johnny? What you can't lay your hands on?

76
00:07:30,797 --> 00:07:34,567
Just put your pickle on everybody's plate, and leave the hard stuff to me.

77
00:07:41,241 --> 00:07:43,810
Sit down and I'll get you some wine.

78
00:07:44,677 --> 00:07:46,212
Thank you, Max.

79
00:07:49,516 --> 00:07:51,251
This is Dr. and Mrs. Houseman.

80
00:07:51,351 --> 00:07:55,388
Baby, Lisa, this is your waiter, Robbie Gould.

81
00:07:55,488 --> 00:07:58,158
Yale medical school.

82
00:07:58,224 --> 00:08:02,162
These people are my special guests. Give them anything they want.

83
00:08:02,195 --> 00:08:04,164
- Enjoy. - Thanks, Max.

84
00:08:08,868 --> 00:08:13,073
Look at all this leftover food. Are there still starving children in Europe?

85
00:08:13,173 --> 00:08:15,875
- Try Southeast Asia, Ma. - Right.

86
00:08:15,975 --> 00:08:18,545
Robbie, Baby wants to send her leftover pot roast...

87
00:08:18,611 --> 00:08:21,748
to Southeast Asia, so anything you don't finish, wrap up.

88
00:08:22,682 --> 00:08:25,285
Max, our Baby's gonna change the world.

89
00:08:25,385 --> 00:08:28,722
- And what are you gonna do, Missy? - Lisa's gonna decorate it.

90
00:08:28,822 --> 00:08:30,890
She already does.

91
00:08:32,892 --> 00:08:36,830
Doc, I want you to meet someone. My grandson Neil.

92
00:08:36,896 --> 00:08:39,299
Goes to the Cornell School of Hotel Management.

93
00:08:39,399 --> 00:08:41,634
Baby's starting Mount Holyoke in the fall.

94
00:08:42,635 --> 00:08:44,371
Oh, great.

95
00:08:53,046 --> 00:08:54,614
Are you going to major in English?

96
00:08:54,714 --> 00:08:58,151
No. Economics of underdeveloped countries.

97
00:08:58,218 --> 00:09:01,621
- I'm going into the Peace Corps. - After the final show...

98
00:09:01,721 --> 00:09:05,492
I'm going to Mississippi with a couple of busboys, freedom ride.

99
00:09:24,911 --> 00:09:27,480
This is our own Tito Suarez.

100
00:10:14,728 --> 00:10:17,163
Mambo! Yeah! Come on!

101
00:10:24,404 --> 00:10:26,539
Who's that?

102
00:10:26,573 --> 00:10:29,042
Oh, them. They're the dance people.

103
00:10:29,109 --> 00:10:32,112
They're here to keep the guests happy.

104
00:10:54,768 --> 00:10:58,905
They shouldn't show off with each other. That's not gonna sell lessons.

105
00:12:15,815 --> 00:12:18,385
- Hi, kids. Having fun? - Yeah.

106
00:12:18,451 --> 00:12:22,322
Actually, I've gotta excuse myself. I'm in charge of the games tonight.

107
00:12:22,389 --> 00:12:25,125
Would you like to help me get things started?

108
00:12:25,158 --> 00:12:26,860
Sure she would.

109
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:38,304
This'll only hurt for a minute. You've got Blue Cross, right?

110
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,183
Was that good for you?

111
00:12:50,216 --> 00:12:53,853
And for being such a good sport, here you go!

112
00:12:59,659 --> 00:13:02,328
I finally met a girl exactly like my mother.

113
00:13:02,429 --> 00:13:05,498
Dresses like her, acts like her. So I brought her home.

114
00:13:05,532 --> 00:13:07,500
My father doesn't like her!

115
00:13:09,235 --> 00:13:11,071
Go figure.

116
00:14:00,053 --> 00:14:02,689
- Hi. - How'd you get here?

117
00:14:02,722 --> 00:14:04,357
- I was taking a walk. - Go back.

118
00:14:04,391 --> 00:14:06,393
Let me help you. What's up there?

119
00:14:06,493 --> 00:14:08,395
No guests allowed. House rules.

120
00:14:08,495 --> 00:14:12,932
Why don't you go back to the playhouse? I saw you dancing with little boss man.

121
00:14:17,771 --> 00:14:19,739
Can you keep a secret?

122
00:14:22,042 --> 00:14:24,577
Your parents would kill you.

123
00:14:24,677 --> 00:14:26,579
Max would kill me.

124
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:22,001
Where'd they learn to do that?

125
00:15:22,102 --> 00:15:23,937
Where?

126
00:15:24,003 --> 00:15:27,006
I don't know. Kids are doing it in their basements back home.

127
00:15:28,308 --> 00:15:30,276
Wanna try it?

128
00:15:31,111 --> 00:15:33,046
Come on, Baby.

129
00:16:10,016 --> 00:16:13,153
Can you imagine dancing like this on the main floor...

130
00:16:13,219 --> 00:16:15,655
home of the family fox-trot?

131
00:16:15,688 --> 00:16:18,224
Max would close the place down first.

132
00:16:50,356 --> 00:16:52,625
That's my cousin, Johnny Castle.

133
00:16:53,460 --> 00:16:55,762
He got me the job here.

134
00:17:14,781 --> 00:17:17,283
- They look great together. - Yeah.

135
00:17:17,317 --> 00:17:19,786
You'd think they were a couple, wouldn't you?

136
00:17:19,853 --> 00:17:23,623
- Aren't they? - No, not since we were kids.

137
00:18:03,329 --> 00:18:03,363
Do you love me?

138
00:18:03,363 --> 00:18:05,265
Do you love me?

139
00:18:24,984 --> 00:18:27,854
Yo, cousin, what's she doing here?

140
00:18:28,521 --> 00:18:31,191
She came with me. She's with me.

141
00:18:31,257 --> 00:18:33,093
I carried a watermelon.

142
00:18:39,099 --> 00:18:41,167
I carried a watermelon?

143
00:19:14,901 --> 00:19:17,070
Bend your knees. Down.

144
00:19:21,741 --> 00:19:23,309
Watch. Watch my eyes.

145
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:25,879
Good.

146
00:19:30,016 --> 00:19:31,551
That's better.

147
00:19:36,423 --> 00:19:38,391
Good. Now roll this way.

148
00:19:40,260 --> 00:19:41,895
Now watch.

149
00:19:51,905 --> 00:19:53,573
Look.

150
00:20:04,384 --> 00:20:06,119
Love man!

151
00:20:41,788 --> 00:20:45,258
Ladies, join our hair-raising wig show.

152
00:20:45,325 --> 00:20:47,293
Try your Sandra Dee, Jackie Kennedy...

153
00:20:47,394 --> 00:20:50,096
or Elizabeth Taylor-Cleopatra wig.

154
00:20:50,130 --> 00:20:53,633
- I'll knock with three. - Look at that cute fella.

155
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,969
Look at these hands. They're golden hands.

156
00:20:58,671 --> 00:21:01,641
My God, it's Cleopatra! I feel like such an ""asp"".

157
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:03,977
You look ten years younger.

158
00:21:04,044 --> 00:21:06,980
At 10:.15, by the pool, we have calisthenics.

159
00:21:07,013 --> 00:21:10,316
Then on the west porch, we have a symposium by Rabbi Maurice Sherman...

160
00:21:10,417 --> 00:21:13,319
on the psychology of insult comedians.

161
00:21:15,055 --> 00:21:18,058
So I say, ""Ask not what your waiter can do for you...

162
00:21:18,158 --> 00:21:20,627
but what you can do for your waiter.""

163
00:21:20,693 --> 00:21:23,663
If tips keep up, I'll have enough for my Alfa Romeo.

164
00:21:25,065 --> 00:21:26,900
That's my favorite car.

165
00:21:29,069 --> 00:21:31,337
Ladies, you look very lovely.

166
00:21:32,439 --> 00:21:36,309
Baby, would you cover for me tonight? Tell Mom and Dad I went to lie down.

167
00:21:36,342 --> 00:21:38,144
Where are you going?

168
00:21:38,211 --> 00:21:42,182
To the golf course. There's a pretty view from the first tee.

169
00:21:45,385 --> 00:21:47,721
Good. Thanks.

170
00:21:54,828 --> 00:21:58,031
So you were really a Rockette?

171
00:21:58,098 --> 00:22:00,166
I think you're a wonderful dancer.

172
00:22:00,233 --> 00:22:03,670
Yeah? Well, my mother kicked me out when I was 16.

173
00:22:03,703 --> 00:22:07,374
I've been dancing ever since. It's the only thing I ever wanted to do anyway.

174
00:22:08,742 --> 00:22:10,677
I envy you.

175
00:22:34,534 --> 00:22:38,571
- Aren't you dancing, Doc? - We're waiting for a waltz.

176
00:22:40,106 --> 00:22:44,144
Hi, Max. Aren't my dance lessons starting to pay off?

177
00:22:44,210 --> 00:22:47,714
You look great, Vivian! Terrific!

178
00:22:50,950 --> 00:22:54,888
That's Vivian Pressman, one of the bungalow bunnies.

179
00:22:56,556 --> 00:22:59,526
That's what we call the women who stay here all week.

180
00:23:00,326 --> 00:23:03,263
The husbands only come up on weekends.

181
00:23:03,329 --> 00:23:06,699
Moe Pressman's a big card player. He'll join our game.

182
00:23:08,301 --> 00:23:11,104
- Moe coming up on Friday? - Friday.

183
00:23:12,072 --> 00:23:14,441
He's away a lot. I know.

184
00:23:15,742 --> 00:23:17,744
It's a hardship.

185
00:23:23,883 --> 00:23:27,454
Where's Penny? Everybody's been asking for her.

186
00:23:28,922 --> 00:23:32,892
What do you mean, where's Penny? She's taking a break.

187
00:23:32,926 --> 00:23:35,462
As long as it's not an all-night break.

188
00:23:39,599 --> 00:23:42,135
Come on, doll. Let's take a walk.

189
00:23:51,544 --> 00:23:54,981
I love to watch your hair blowing in the breeze.

190
00:23:58,551 --> 00:24:00,820
Maybe my parents are looking for me.

191
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,655
Baby, don't worry.

192
00:24:02,756 --> 00:24:06,493
If they think you're with me, they'll be the happiest parents at Kellerman's.

193
00:24:08,695 --> 00:24:10,630
I have to say it.

194
00:24:10,697 --> 00:24:13,700
- I'm known as the catch of the county. - I'm sure you are.

195
00:24:13,767 --> 00:24:16,870
Last week I took a girl away from Jamie, the lifeguard.

196
00:24:16,970 --> 00:24:22,142
And he said to her, ""What does he have that I don't have?""

197
00:24:22,208 --> 00:24:25,512
And she said, ""Two hotels.""

198
00:24:27,547 --> 00:24:28,681
Robbie.

199
00:24:29,582 --> 00:24:31,584
I don't hear an apology.

200
00:24:31,684 --> 00:24:36,890
Go back to Mommy and Daddy and listen. Maybe you'll hear one in your dreams.

201
00:24:39,059 --> 00:24:41,861
I'm sorry you had to see that, Baby.

202
00:24:42,796 --> 00:24:45,231
Sometimes in this world...

203
00:24:45,331 --> 00:24:47,867
you see things you don't wanna see.

204
00:24:52,439 --> 00:24:54,374
You hungry?

205
00:24:55,241 --> 00:24:56,876
Come on.

206
00:25:02,916 --> 00:25:06,886
So, Baby, what do you want? You can have anything you want.

207
00:25:08,088 --> 00:25:10,690
A brownie, some milk...

208
00:25:10,757 --> 00:25:14,260
Ieftover rice pudding, beets...

209
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:16,062
cabbage roll...

210
00:25:20,266 --> 00:25:22,602
fruit salad, sweet gherkins?

211
00:25:22,635 --> 00:25:26,740
Neil, look, I'm sorry. I better go check on Lisa.

212
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:28,575
Yeah.

213
00:25:58,304 --> 00:26:01,307
- Why's she here? - In case Neil comes back.

214
00:26:01,341 --> 00:26:03,443
Penny just doesn't think.

215
00:26:03,510 --> 00:26:06,479
She wouldn't do anything stupid, would she?

216
00:26:07,313 --> 00:26:11,051
So, what's wrong? What's the matter with her?

217
00:26:12,085 --> 00:26:14,587
- She's knocked up, Baby. - Billy!

218
00:26:16,289 --> 00:26:20,260
- What's he gonna do about it? - ""What's he gonna do about it?""

219
00:26:20,994 --> 00:26:22,595
It's mine, right?

220
00:26:22,662 --> 00:26:25,331
- Right away you think it's mine. - But I thought...

221
00:26:42,982 --> 00:26:45,652
It's okay. Johnny's here.

222
00:26:50,156 --> 00:26:52,659
I'm never gonna let anything happen to you.

223
00:26:56,896 --> 00:26:58,832
We got to go.

224
00:27:00,967 --> 00:27:03,336
Just hold on. Just hold on.

225
00:27:03,370 --> 00:27:05,972
Good girl. Good girl.

226
00:27:10,577 --> 00:27:13,580
What do you think you're doing? You're in trouble, you talk to me.

227
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:16,116
I'll take care of it.

228
00:27:16,182 --> 00:27:19,686
You should've come to me in the first place.

229
00:27:19,753 --> 00:27:23,156
Forget it, Johnny. I'm not taking what's left of your salary.

230
00:27:23,189 --> 00:27:27,160
- Penny, that's my business. - Besides, it wouldn't be enough.

231
00:27:37,003 --> 00:27:39,406
Oh, God, it's hopeless!

232
00:27:39,506 --> 00:27:41,674
Don't say that.

233
00:27:41,708 --> 00:27:44,711
There's gotta be a way to work it out.

234
00:27:47,313 --> 00:27:50,683
Baby? Is that your name?

235
00:27:51,584 --> 00:27:53,353
You know what, Baby?

236
00:27:54,387 --> 00:27:56,856
You don't know shit about my problems.

237
00:27:58,058 --> 00:28:00,026
I told her.

238
00:28:00,093 --> 00:28:05,565
Jesus! She's gonna tell her management boyfriend and then we'll all get fired.

239
00:28:05,632 --> 00:28:09,936
Why not skywrite it? ""Penny got knocked up by Robbie, the creep.""

240
00:28:10,036 --> 00:28:12,639
- Look-- - No, Baby.

241
00:28:13,873 --> 00:28:16,710
One of the counselors knows a doctor, a real M.D....

242
00:28:16,776 --> 00:28:19,779
just traveling through New Paltz one day next week.

243
00:28:19,879 --> 00:28:22,649
We can get an appointment, but it costs $250.

244
00:28:22,716 --> 00:28:26,352
But if it's Robbie, there's no problem. I know he has the money.

245
00:28:26,419 --> 00:28:28,888
- I'm sure if you tell him-- - He knows.

246
00:28:36,429 --> 00:28:40,500
Go back to your playpen, Baby.

247
00:28:50,410 --> 00:28:50,477
- Why should you tell me what's right? - You can't just leave her.

248
00:28:50,477 --> 00:28:54,080
- Why should you tell me what's right? - You can't just leave her.

249
00:28:54,147 --> 00:28:57,650
I didn't blow a summer hauling bagels just to bail out some chick...

250
00:28:57,751 --> 00:29:00,019
