01:00:45,258 --> 01:00:47,594
You couldn't have. It's okay.

504
01:00:59,606 --> 01:01:02,409
- So, how you doin'? - I'm okay.

505
01:01:03,977 --> 01:01:06,446
Dr. Houseman says I'm going to be fine.

506
01:01:07,781 --> 01:01:11,584
- I can still have children. - Oh, Penny, that's really great.

507
01:01:14,154 --> 01:01:16,923
So, how did it go last night?

508
01:01:16,990 --> 01:01:18,958
Good.

509
01:01:20,260 --> 01:01:24,764
Fine. I didn't do the lifts, but it was good.

510
01:01:35,475 --> 01:01:40,180
Well, I guess I gonna go.

511
01:01:42,348 --> 01:01:43,983
See ya.

512
01:01:52,058 --> 01:01:54,360
- So, he says you're going to be fine? - What are you doing?

513
01:01:54,461 --> 01:01:57,897
- I'll tell Max your grandmother died. - How many times have you told me...

514
01:01:57,997 --> 01:02:00,734
never get mixed-up with them?

515
01:02:00,834 --> 01:02:02,736
I know what I'm doing.

516
01:02:03,837 --> 01:02:07,607
You listen to me. You've got to stop it now.

517
01:02:23,556 --> 01:02:26,760
Look, I gotta run. I got a lesson with the Kramers.

518
01:02:26,860 --> 01:02:29,229
They'll kill each other if I'm not there.

519
01:02:29,295 --> 01:02:31,731
Well, sure. You've gotta go.

520
01:02:34,534 --> 01:02:35,935
I'll see ya.

521
01:02:55,488 --> 01:02:58,391
It's rainy day game time. Pin the tail on the guest.

522
01:02:58,491 --> 01:03:00,894
Win ten boxes of Kleenex or a billy goat!

523
01:03:01,961 --> 01:03:05,432
God, I am so sick of this rain.

524
01:03:05,532 --> 01:03:08,234
Remind me not to take my honeymoon at Niagara Falls.

525
01:03:08,301 --> 01:03:11,438
So, you go to Acapulco. It'll be fine.

526
01:03:11,504 --> 01:03:15,141
Where is my beige iridescent lipstick?

527
01:03:15,241 --> 01:03:17,410
I know I put it in this drawer.

528
01:03:17,510 --> 01:03:19,713
Baby, where are you going in this weather?

529
01:03:19,779 --> 01:03:22,382
Uh, they're having charades in the west lobby.

530
01:03:22,449 --> 01:03:25,385
Quite the little joiner, aren't we?

531
01:03:40,166 --> 01:03:43,536
- Have you had many women? - What?

532
01:03:46,306 --> 01:03:48,141
Baby, come on.

533
01:03:48,174 --> 01:03:50,143
Tell me. I want to know.

534
01:04:01,988 --> 01:04:04,124
You gotta understand what it's like.

535
01:04:04,190 --> 01:04:06,626
You come from the streets and suddenly you're up here.

536
01:04:06,726 --> 01:04:10,597
Women are throwing themselves at you and they smell so good.

537
01:04:10,663 --> 01:04:12,766
They really take care of themselves.

538
01:04:12,832 --> 01:04:15,268
I never knew women could be like that.

539
01:04:15,335 --> 01:04:18,605
They're so goddamn rich you think they must know about everything.

540
01:04:18,671 --> 01:04:21,374
They're slippin' their room keys in my hand two and three times a day--

541
01:04:21,441 --> 01:04:25,645
different women-- so, I think I'm scorin' big, right?

542
01:04:25,745 --> 01:04:30,150
You think, ""They wouldn't be doing this if they didn't care about me, right?""

543
01:04:31,351 --> 01:04:34,320
That's all right. I understand. You were just using them, that's all.

544
01:04:36,289 --> 01:04:37,757
No, that's not it.

545
01:04:38,658 --> 01:04:40,960
That's the thing. It wasn't like that.

546
01:04:43,063 --> 01:04:45,165
They were using me.

547
01:05:12,726 --> 01:05:14,661
What's your real name, Baby?

548
01:05:16,663 --> 01:05:20,834
Frances, for the first woman in the Cabinet.

549
01:05:23,036 --> 01:05:26,406
Frances. That's a real grownup name.

550
01:05:39,586 --> 01:05:42,021
I've decided to go all the way with Robbie.

551
01:05:44,591 --> 01:05:48,294
No, not with someone like him.

552
01:05:48,361 --> 01:05:52,732
Do you think if we came back for a ten-year anniversary, it would be free?

553
01:05:52,832 --> 01:05:56,302
It's just wrong this way. It should be with someone--

554
01:05:56,403 --> 01:06:01,007
With someone that you sort of love.

555
01:06:01,041 --> 01:06:05,278
Come on. You don't care about me.

556
01:06:05,378 --> 01:06:08,381
You wouldn't care if I humped the entire army...

557
01:06:08,448 --> 01:06:11,618
as long as we were on the right side of the Ho Chi Minh Trail.

558
01:06:11,718 --> 01:06:16,556
What you care about is that you're not Daddy's girl anymore.

559
01:06:16,589 --> 01:06:19,059
He listens when I talk now.

560
01:06:20,193 --> 01:06:21,594
You hate that.

561
01:06:38,778 --> 01:06:41,514
Two, three, cha-cha-cha.

562
01:06:41,614 --> 01:06:44,484
My frame. Where's my pleasing arc?

563
01:06:44,584 --> 01:06:48,121
Spaghetti arms! Would you give me some tension, please?

564
01:06:49,989 --> 01:06:53,359
You're invading my dance space. This is my dance space.

565
01:06:53,426 --> 01:06:55,829
That's yours. Let's cha-cha.

566
01:07:02,001 --> 01:07:04,671
Don't look down. Look right here.

567
01:07:13,613 --> 01:07:18,351
- How you call your lover boy? - Come here, lover boy.

568
01:07:18,451 --> 01:07:21,988
- And if he doesn't answer? - Oh, lover boy.

569
01:07:22,088 --> 01:07:25,458
- And if still doesn't answer? - I simply say...

570
01:07:25,492 --> 01:07:28,261
Baby

571
01:07:28,328 --> 01:07:31,164
O-Oh, baby

572
01:07:32,265 --> 01:07:35,101
My sweet baby

573
01:07:36,136 --> 01:07:38,104
You're the one

574
01:07:53,486 --> 01:07:54,988
Takin' dance lessons?

575
01:07:56,022 --> 01:07:57,991
I could teach ya, kid.

576
01:08:02,695 --> 01:08:05,665
My grandfather put me in charge of the final show.

577
01:08:05,732 --> 01:08:08,034
I want to talk to you about the last dance.

578
01:08:08,134 --> 01:08:11,204
I'd like to shake things up a bit.

579
01:08:11,304 --> 01:08:13,907
You know, move with the times.

580
01:08:14,007 --> 01:08:16,009
I've got a lot of ideas.

581
01:08:16,076 --> 01:08:18,178
I've been working with the staff kids...

582
01:08:18,211 --> 01:08:21,748
on a cross between a Cuban rhythm and soul dancing.

583
01:08:21,848 --> 01:08:24,617
Whoa, boy.

584
01:08:24,718 --> 01:08:26,953
Way over your head here.

585
01:08:27,053 --> 01:08:31,024
You always do the mambo, huh?

586
01:08:31,091 --> 01:08:34,327
Why not dance this year's final dance...

587
01:08:36,362 --> 01:08:38,231
to the pachenga?

588
01:08:39,399 --> 01:08:40,533
Right.

589
01:08:42,736 --> 01:08:46,439
Well, you're free to do the same, tired number as last year if you want...

590
01:08:46,539 --> 01:08:49,442
but next year we'll find another dance person...

591
01:08:49,542 --> 01:08:51,911
- who'll only be too happy-- - Sure, Neil. No problem.

592
01:08:54,114 --> 01:08:56,282
We'll end the season with the pachenga.

593
01:08:56,383 --> 01:08:57,817
Great idea.

594
01:09:04,391 --> 01:09:08,762
Sometimes he's hard to talk to, but the ladies seem to like him.

595
01:09:08,795 --> 01:09:11,798
See that he gives you the full half-hour you're paying him for, kid.

596
01:09:20,673 --> 01:09:23,743
That little wimp. He wouldn't know a new idea if it hit him in the pachenga.

597
01:09:23,810 --> 01:09:26,112
I could have told him some new ideas.

598
01:09:26,212 --> 01:09:28,214
Why did you let him talk to you that way?

599
01:09:28,281 --> 01:09:30,750
- What, fight the boss man? - You tell him your ideas.

600
01:09:30,817 --> 01:09:33,620
- He's a person like everyone else. - Look, I know these people.

601
01:09:33,686 --> 01:09:36,389
They are rich and they're mean. They won't listen to me.

602
01:09:36,456 --> 01:09:38,858
Why not fight harder? Make them listen.

603
01:09:38,958 --> 01:09:41,828
Because I need this goddamned job lined up for next summer.

604
01:09:42,929 --> 01:09:44,998
My dad calls me today.

605
01:09:45,098 --> 01:09:47,701
""Good news,"" he says. ""Uncle Paul can finally get you in the union.""

606
01:09:47,801 --> 01:09:49,035
What union?

607
01:09:50,236 --> 01:09:54,140
The House Painters and Plasterers Local Number 179 at your service.

608
01:10:02,282 --> 01:10:04,818
I've been thinking a lot about the Domino Theory.

609
01:10:04,884 --> 01:10:07,253
Now, when Viet Nam falls, is China Next?

610
01:10:10,056 --> 01:10:11,991
I don't think they saw us.

611
01:10:23,169 --> 01:10:24,637
Fight harder, huh?

612
01:10:25,672 --> 01:10:29,442
I don't see you fightin' so hard, tellin' Daddy I'm your guy.

613
01:10:29,509 --> 01:10:31,678
I will. With my father, it's complicated.

614
01:10:31,745 --> 01:10:34,180
- I will tell him. - I don't believe you, Baby.

615
01:10:37,851 --> 01:10:39,319
I don't think...

616
01:10:40,854 --> 01:10:43,623
that you ever had any intention of telling him.

617
01:10:44,691 --> 01:10:45,825
Ever.

618
01:10:56,870 --> 01:10:56,870
Well, Cousin, it's almost over. Labor Day weekend is here.

619
01:10:56,870 --> 01:10:59,706
Well, Cousin, it's almost over. Labor Day weekend is here.

620
01:10:59,739 --> 01:11:03,476
Soon it's back to the old books and back to work. What a terrible thought!

621
01:11:13,219 --> 01:11:15,188
Have you seen Johnny?

622
01:11:30,970 --> 01:11:32,272
I'm sorry.

623
01:11:36,743 --> 01:11:38,678
Looks like I picked the wrong sister.

624
01:11:38,745 --> 01:11:41,548
That's okay, Baby. I went slummin' too.

625
01:11:59,399 --> 01:12:01,067
Hit me.

626
01:12:08,141 --> 01:12:10,110
Get out of here. You're not worth it.

627
01:13:08,301 --> 01:13:10,503
Win big, Moe.

628
01:13:10,603 --> 01:13:11,838
As always.

629
01:13:29,389 --> 01:13:33,226
This is our last night together, lover. I've got something worked out for us.

630
01:13:55,882 --> 01:13:58,184
Excuse me, sir. The pirate number's next.

631
01:13:58,251 --> 01:14:00,553
Oh, thanks. Hey, kid.

632
01:14:00,620 --> 01:14:03,356
I've been playing cards all weekend and I've got an all-night game tonight.

633
01:14:03,423 --> 01:14:06,926
Why don't you give my wife some extra dance lessons?

634
01:14:16,002 --> 01:14:17,904
I'm sorry, Mr. Pressman...

635
01:14:18,004 --> 01:14:20,473
but I'm booked up for the whole weekend with the show.

636
01:14:20,573 --> 01:14:22,776
I won't have time for anything else.

637
01:14:22,842 --> 01:14:26,046
I don't think it'd be fair to take the money.

638
01:14:50,804 --> 01:14:53,640
I've decided tonight's the night with Robbie.

639
01:14:53,673 --> 01:14:55,875
He doesn't even know yet.

640
01:15:31,611 --> 01:15:32,846
It's me.

641
01:15:38,017 --> 01:15:39,352
Holy shit!

642
01:16:00,407 --> 01:16:02,509
You wanna hear somethin' crazy?

643
01:16:06,846 --> 01:16:08,314
Last night l--

644
01:16:09,482 --> 01:16:13,753
I dreamt we were walking along and we met your father.

645
01:16:13,820 --> 01:16:16,489
He said, ""Come on,"" and he put his arm around me.

646
01:16:18,191 --> 01:16:20,293
Just like he did with Robbie.

647
01:17:07,574 --> 01:17:12,812
You know how you feel when you see a patient and you think he's all right...

648
01:17:12,912 --> 01:17:15,882
then you look at the X rays and it's nothing like you thought?

649
01:17:15,915 --> 01:17:17,183
What happened?

650
01:17:17,250 --> 01:17:20,720
It's exactly what it's like when you find out one of your staff's a thief.

651
01:17:20,754 --> 01:17:24,424
Moe Pressman's wallet was stolen when he was playing pinochle last night.

652
01:17:24,524 --> 01:17:27,527
It was in his jacket hanging on the back of his chair.

653
01:17:27,594 --> 01:17:31,831
He had it at 1:30 and when he checked again at quarter of 4::00...

654
01:17:31,898 --> 01:17:34,300
it was missing.

655
01:17:34,401 --> 01:17:38,905
Vivian thinks she remembers this dance kid Johnny...

656
01:17:38,972 --> 01:17:40,240
walking by.

657
01:17:41,307 --> 01:17:45,211
So we ask him, ""You have an alibi for last night?""

658
01:17:45,245 --> 01:17:47,480
He says he was alone in his room reading.

659
01:17:48,848 --> 01:17:51,284
There are no books in Johnny's room!

660
01:17:53,253 --> 01:17:55,321
There's been a mistake. I know Johnny didn't do it.

661
01:17:55,422 --> 01:17:57,857
There's been similar thefts at the Sheldrake. It's happened here before.

662
01:17:57,924 --> 01:18:00,293
- Three other wallets. - I know he didn't do it.

663
01:18:00,393 --> 01:18:02,462
Stay out of it, Baby.

664
01:18:02,562 --> 01:18:06,399
Wait. Don't put those tables together. Come on.

665
01:18:08,635 --> 01:18:12,706
Daddy, I need your help. I know Johnny didn't take Moe's wallet.

666
01:18:12,772 --> 01:18:15,141
- Oh? How do you know? - I can't tell you.

667
01:18:15,241 --> 01:18:20,013
- Just please trust me, Daddy. - I'm sorry, Baby. I can't.

668
01:18:20,113 --> 01:18:22,182
This Danish is pure protein.

669
01:18:25,018 --> 01:18:28,722
Maybe Johnny didn't do it. Anyone could've taken it.

670
01:18:28,788 --> 01:18:30,724
Maybe it was, uh--

671
01:18:30,790 --> 01:18:33,660
It could've been that little, old couple, the Schumachers.

672
01:18:33,727 --> 01:18:36,963
- I saw her with a couple of wallets. - Sylvia and Sidney?

673
01:18:37,030 --> 01:18:40,066
Baby, you don't go around accusing innocent people.

674
01:18:40,166 --> 01:18:44,637
I even saw them at the Sheldrake. You said something was stolen from there.

675
01:18:44,704 --> 01:18:48,308
I got an eyewitness and the kid has no alibi.

676
01:18:48,375 --> 01:18:52,312
Come on, Neil. You'll learn what it's like to fire an employee.

677
01:18:53,513 --> 01:18:57,016
Wait a minute. I know Johnny didn't take the wallet.

678
01:18:57,083 --> 01:19:00,320
I know because he was in his room all night.

679
01:19:00,387 --> 01:19:04,891
And the reason I know is because I was with him.

680
01:19:29,315 --> 01:19:31,217
I told you I was telling the truth.

681
01:19:36,089 --> 01:19:38,058
I'm sorry I lied to you.

682
01:19:40,927 --> 01:19:42,896
But you lied too.

683
01:19:45,098 --> 01:19:48,668
You told me everyone was alike and deserved a fair break.

684
01:19:48,735 --> 01:19:50,837
But you meant everyone who is like you.

685
01:19:53,573 --> 01:19:56,843
You told me you wanted me to change the world, to make it better.

686
01:19:57,911 --> 01:20:00,547
But you meant by becoming a lawyer or an economist...

687
01:20:00,580 --> 01:20:02,749
and marrying someone from Harvard.

688
01:20:05,418 --> 01:20:07,954
I'm not proud of myself.

689
01:20:08,054 --> 01:20:11,558
But I'm in this family too. You can't keep giving me the silent treatment.

690
01:20:15,095 --> 01:20:17,931
There are a lot of things about me that aren't what you thought.

691
01:20:18,965 --> 01:20:21,935
But if you love me, you have to love all the things about me.

692
01:20:24,604 --> 01:20:26,539
And I love you.

693
01:20:26,606 --> 01:20:31,177
I'm sorry I let you down. I'm so sorry, Daddy.

694
01:20:32,078 --> 01:20:34,314
But you let me down too.

695
01:21:04,611 --> 01:21:06,813
I have been lookin' for you all over.

696
01:21:07,814 --> 01:21:09,649
They found the Schumachers.

697
01:21:09,749 --> 01:21:12,052
Fingerprinted their water glasses.

698
01:21:12,152 --> 01:21:14,988
Found out they were wanted in Arizona and in Florida...

699
01:21:15,055 --> 01:21:17,490
and they made a fortune here this summer.

700
01:21:17,524 --> 01:21:19,492
So then it's all right.

701
01:21:20,627 --> 01:21:22,629
I knew it would work out.

702
01:21:22,695 --> 01:21:24,998
- I knew they'd have to apologize. - I'm out, Baby.

703
01:21:30,236 --> 01:21:32,172
They fired you anyway because of me.

704
01:21:33,840 --> 01:21:37,177
And if I leave quietly, I'll get my summer bonus.

705
01:21:40,180 --> 01:21:42,082
So I did it for nothing.

706
01:21:42,182 --> 01:21:46,186
I hurt my family, you lost your job anyway-- I did it for nothing!

707
01:21:46,252 --> 01:21:48,188
No, not for nothing.

708
01:21:48,254 --> 01:21:51,624
Nobody has ever done anything like that for me before.

709
01:21:52,392 --> 01:21:55,628
You were right. You can't win no matter what you do.

710
01:21:55,695 --> 01:21:59,165
Listen to me. I don't want to hear that from you. You can.

711
01:22:01,067 --> 01:22:03,169
I used to think so.

712
01:22:24,758 --> 01:22:26,860
Dr. Houseman, can l, uh--

713
01:22:28,361 --> 01:22:31,398
Look, I'm going anyway and I know what you must be thinking.

714
01:22:31,464 --> 01:22:34,434
You don't know anything at all about me.

715
01:22:34,534 --> 01:22:37,237
I know you want Baby to be like you.

716
01:22:37,270 --> 01:22:40,106
The kind of person people look up to.

717
01:22:40,206 --> 01:22:42,409
Baby is like that. If you could just see--

718
01:22:42,442 --> 01:22:45,412
Don't you tell me what to see.

719
01:22:45,445 --> 01:22:48,081
I see someone in front of me who got his partner in trouble...

720
01:22:48,114 --> 01:22:50,550
and sent her off to some butcher...

721
01:22:50,617 --> 01:22:53,887
while he moved on to an innocent, young girl like my daughter.

722
01:22:59,059 --> 01:23:01,661
Yeah, I guess that's what you would see.

723
01:23:17,210 --> 01:23:20,480
I can't imagine being here without you even one day.

724
01:23:20,513 --> 01:23:24,284
Just think, you have more time for horseshoes and croquet.

725
01:23:27,220 --> 01:23:29,956
Maybe they'll saw you in seven pieces now.

726
01:23:32,358 --> 01:23:34,461
I guess we surprised everybody.

727
01:23:36,830 --> 01:23:38,765
I guess we did.

728
01:23:46,773 --> 01:23:48,675
Hardly would be sorry.

729
01:23:50,710 --> 01:23:52,178
Neither will l.

730
01:23:59,552 --> 01:24:00,987
I'll see ya.

731
01:24:57,177 --> 01:24:59,145
I'll do your hair.

732
01:25:01,247 --> 01:25:03,349
It could look pretty if--

733
01:25:09,255 --> 01:25:11,691
You're prettier your way.

734
01:25:11,758 --> 01:25:13,026
This way.

735
01:25:35,715 --> 01:25:39,986
Kellermans, we come together

736
01:25:40,086 --> 01:25:44,090
Singing all as one

737
01:25:44,190 --> 01:25:48,294
We have shared another season's

738
01:25:48,361 --> 01:25:52,298
Talent, play and fun

739
01:25:52,365 --> 01:25:56,469
Summer days will soon be over

740
01:25:56,569 --> 01:26:00,673
Soon the autumn starts

741
01:26:00,774 --> 01:26:04,677
And tonight the memories whisper

742
01:26:04,778 --> 01:26:08,148
Softly in our hearts

743
01:26:09,215 --> 01:26:13,086
Join hands and hearts and voices

744
01:26:13,153 --> 01:26:16,556
Voices, hearts and hands

745
01:26:16,623 --> 01:26:20,560
At Kellerman's the friendships last

746
01:26:20,627 --> 01:26:25,165
Long as the mountain stands

747
01:26:25,231 --> 01:26:29,502
Daytime, nighttime, any hour

748
01:26:29,569 --> 01:26:33,440
Weather rain or shine

749
01:26:33,506 --> 01:26:37,711
Games and lectures Jokes and music

750
01:26:37,777 --> 01:26:41,848
Happily combine

751
01:26:55,261 --> 01:26:57,163
Good luck in medical school, son.

752
01:26:59,365 --> 01:27:01,901
And I wanted to thank you for your help with the Penny situation.

753
01:27:01,968 --> 01:27:05,805
- I guess we've all gotten into messes. - What?

754
01:27:07,507 --> 01:27:10,310
I thought Baby told you. Look, I'm not sure.

755
01:27:10,377 --> 01:27:13,613
Penny said so, but you know with girls like that. They're liable to pin it...

756
01:27:13,646 --> 01:27:15,615
on any guy around.

757
01:27:21,855 --> 01:27:24,457
- What's the hot tip for the day? - Finished.

758
01:27:25,525 --> 01:27:28,395
You and me, Tito. We've seen it all, eh?

759
01:27:28,495 --> 01:27:33,566
Bubbah and Zeda serving the first pasteurized milk to the boarders.

760
01:27:33,666 --> 01:27:35,835
Through the war years when we didn't have any meat.

761
01:27:35,902 --> 01:27:38,638
Through the Depression when we didn't have anything.

762
01:27:38,671 --> 01:27:41,174
Lots of changes, though, Max.

763
01:27:41,207 --> 01:27:44,711
It's not the changes so much this time.

764
01:27:44,778 --> 01:27:47,347
It's that it all seems to be ending.

765
01:27:47,414 --> 01:27:51,418
You think kids want to come with their parents and take fox-trot lessons?

766
01:27:51,518 --> 01:27:54,654
Trips to Europe, that's what the kids want.

767
01:27:55,722 --> 01:27:58,291
Twenty-two countries in three days.

768
01:27:59,392 --> 01:28:01,661
It feels like it's all slipping away.

769
01:28:02,862 --> 01:28:06,733
But the heartbeats of vacation

770
01:28:06,833 --> 01:28:10,704
There no cares are seen

771
01:28:10,770 --> 01:28:14,741
So let's join in just one last chorus

772
01:28:14,841 --> 01:28:18,211
Visitors, staff and guests

773
01:28:18,244 --> 01:28:22,782
What we've shared won't be forgotten

774
01:28:22,882 --> 01:28:25,919
Old friends are the best

775
01:29:01,454 --> 01:29:03,189
Nobody puts Baby in the corner.

776
01:29:04,958 --> 01:29:06,359
Come on.

777
01:29:27,113 --> 01:29:29,315
Sorry about the disruption, folks...

778
01:29:29,382 --> 01:29:32,652
but I always do the last dance of the season.

779
01:29:32,752 --> 01:29:35,755
This year somebody told me not to.

780
01:29:35,789 --> 01:29:39,626
So I'm gonna do my kind of dancin' with a great partner...

781
01:29:40,460 --> 01:29:43,363
who's not only a terrific dancer...

782
01:29:43,463 --> 01:29:45,932
but somebody who's taught me that there are people...

783
01:29:45,965 --> 01:29:49,002
willing to stand up for other people no matter what it costs them.

784
01:29:50,370 --> 01:29:52,939
Somebody who's taught me...

785
01:29:54,874 --> 01:29:56,976
about the kind of person I want to be.

786
01:29:58,178 --> 01:29:59,646
Miss Frances Houseman.

787
01:30:00,480 --> 01:30:01,881
Sit down, Jake.

788
01:31:25,732 --> 01:31:27,801
I think she gets this from me.

789
01:34:22,409 --> 01:34:25,211
Do you have sheet music on this stuff?

790
01:34:33,286 --> 01:34:36,389
I know you weren't the one who got Penny in trouble.

791
01:34:38,558 --> 01:34:41,027
When I'm wrong, I say I'm wrong.

792
01:34:47,567 --> 01:34:49,502
You looked wonderful out there.

793
01:35:47,193 --> 01:35:49,295
Now l

794
01:35:49,362 --> 01:35:53,333
Had the time of my life

795
01:35:53,400 --> 01:35:57,570
No, I never felt this way before

796
01:35:57,637 --> 01:36:00,040
Yes, I swear

797
01:36:00,106 --> 01:36:04,644
It's so true And I owe it all to you

